==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Foreigner
<hw>For"eign*er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A person belonging
to or owning allegiance to a foreign country; one not native in the
country or jurisdiction under consideration, or not naturalized there;
an alien; a stranger.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Joy is such a <qex>foreigner</qex>,⟦br⟧
So mere a stranger to my thoughts.</q> <rj><qau>Denham.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Nor could the majesty of the English crown appear in a greater
luster, either to <qex>foreigners</qex> or subjects.</q>
<rj><qau>Swift.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Foreignism</ent>⟦br⟧
